# Contributing Guidelines

Thank you for considering contributing to mostaqem!
 Please take a moment to review these guidelines.

## Reporting Issues & Bugs

- **Check Existing Issues**: Before opening a new issue, please ensure that your issue hasn’t been reported yet.
- **Provide Details**: When reporting an issue, include as much information as possible (e.g., steps to reproduce, environment details, expected vs. actual behavior).
- **Bug Labels**: Add relevant labels to categorize your issue (e.g., `bug`, `enhancement`).

## Requesting Features

- **Feature Requests**: Use the `feature request` template and clearly describe the desired functionality.
- **Be Specific**: Provide context on why the feature is valuable and how it could be implemented.

## Coding Standards

- **Effective Dart Style**: Stick to the [Effective Dart](https://dart.dev/guides/language/effective-dart) guidelines for clean, readable code.
- **Formatting**: Use `dart format` to format your code before submitting a PR.
- **Testing**: Ensure all new features or bug fixes include relevant tests.

## Submitting Pull Requests

- **Branching**: Create a feature branch for your work.
- **Commits**: Write clear and concise commit messages.
- **Pull Request Description**: Describe the purpose of the PR and link any relevant issues.

## Communication

- **Collaborate**: Engage in constructive discussions and provide feedback in code reviews.
- **Be Respectful**: Treat all contributors and their work with respect.

May Allah reward you (جزاك الله خيرا)